Ahhh! It’s almost dinner! What are you having? It comes around so quickly every single day, and it’s summer! You don’t have a lot of time on your hands!

You can make them in the Instant Pot or Slow cooker, or make and extra at the same time, and save it as a freezer meal for later!

Beef Tips and Gravy (one of our favorite freezer meals that you can use in your slow cooker or Instant Pot!)

It is a heat wave! And we do not want to turn on our ovens or grills, so we are surviving on our Instant Pots and Slow Cookers this summer!

These Beef Tips and Gravy are so yummy, full of flavor, and literally take only a few minutes to throw together. Also, we firmly believe this recipe is the secret to a happy marriage! 💕 It’s that good. 

Head to our website to get the full recipe, and save this video for reference!

If you're as serious about peaches as we are, then you know the panic of knowing that you can't possibly eat all of the peaches that you bought from the adorable fruit stand on the side of the road, but cringing at the idea of wasting any of those beautiful juicy peaches! We have been there, and we like to think that we've done our part in preventing peaches from ever going to waste, by coming up with as many ways to use them as possible! One fun way to use those peaches is in our Blueberry Peach breakfast pastry! This pastry is an amazing way to start the day, not to mention SO easy. 

Check out the clickable link in our bio or head to our website and search, “Blueberry Peach Breakfast Pastry".

It's safe to say that Twix might just be the king of the candy world! They're always the candy that parents everywhere *casually* ask their kids about after Halloween trick or treating! However, we're still a little bit torn between Reese's and Twix. Peanut butter and chocolate, or caramel and chocolate?! Stay tuned for the day that we decide. In the meantime though, we have been living for these Homemade Twix Bars! These easy bar desserts are thick, carmely, and topped with lucious chocolate-we might even say they're better than the original! Make these tonight and help us decide between Reese's and Twix in the comments-the conversation needs to be had! 

Check out the clickable link in our bio or head to our website and search, “The BEST Homemade Twix Bars Recipe".
